<br>
I hope to attempt to get this rod soon...last one!<br>
<br>
*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*<br>
<br>
Lower Guk<br>
IMHO the hardest part of the Quest...<br>
I had a friend to help me with this, otherwise i woudn't be able to solve this  <br>
Enter lguk, ask for IvU from a cleric or chanter...make your way to the hand room, and ask someone to train the hand and frog to zone (or get hand/frog killed by someone), while he does that swim up, and grab the rod, and gate out...<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Just want to point out that you don't actually have to train Hand and Dar out of the the room in LGuk. If you cast regular invis (not VU) at the bottom of the room before you go up, the Hand will not be able to see thru it. The Dar will, but you shouldn't get close enough to agro Dar. Should be able to do it w/o getting out of water. I did with Dark Elf so certainly any other races (except maybe Gnome?) should be able to. <br>
<br>
ITU would help if you can get the spell. Otherwise, you can pay a shaman to make you some ITU potions, or get a friendly cleric or necro to cast it on you at the zone(I like to have a few potions as backup, tho).<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~**~<br>
<br>
There are a couple of live frogs near the entrance to Lguk, but usually someone is at the zone pulling them. Get friendly with the folks at the zone, and when the tunnel is clear, you can ITU and head to the Bedroom. If you are very lucky, someone will be camping that as well.<br>
<br>
If not, you will want to hug the left wall when you go past the bats...<br>
<br>
the Hand room -<br>
When I did this part, I went solo during primetime hours. Again, it pays to talk to the people there in /shout or /ooc - find out who is camping what, and if anyone is pulling the Hand room. Let them know about your quest(most regulars in Lguk are familiar with it) and they will generally let you know when the path is clear.<br>
<br>
One of the camps was pulling the Hand room on a regular basis, so I did not have to worry about the mobs in the Hand room itself. I just had to make sure ITU was up for any wanderers I met, and follow the path to the Hand room, swim UP through the inverted well, and pop out to grab the rod, then gate<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~**~*~<br>
<br>
A very good guide!<br>
