<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*<br>
<br>
The Hand Room:<br>
<br>
copy and paste this map in notepad, changing the font to courier:<br>
=========<br>
|-------|<br>
/ \     |<br>
| | H   |<br>
\ / K   |<br>
|-------|<br>
=========<br>
<br>
The circle is the column of water that U swim up though.<br>
It is not a long swim.<br>
There is a ramp to help U enter the water at the bottom.<br>
I believe this ramp is on the side closest to the hand.<br>
The rod spawns in several spots.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
I just said what the heck and expected to die and kamkazied it. I waited until a Saturday evening, there were tons of people in LGuk, no one was camping the hand room or willing to help (or able too). There were lots of people there so all the mobs on the way were occupied. I made it there untouched without IU.<br>
<br>
I bound myself at the bottom (maybe not the best of ideas). Swam up, looked around spotted the rod without getting aggro. Swam back down, buffed up, put up shields, invis and everything else. Swam up, planned my point of attacked and ran for it. Both aggroed on me but I had enough time to jump back in the water and swim to the bottom before I died. Even got a nuke in (I always go down fighting) despite it not landing.<br>
<br>
Died right at my bind point.<br>
<br>
I stayed off for about 5 mins. Went back and was looking right at my corpse..looted, memed a gate and got the heck outta there.<br>
<br>
The only death I had for this quest.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*<br>
<br>
&quot;If this helps one Wizzy get their SoTW I'd be happy&quot;  -me<br>
<br>
Your Humble Noble,<br>
Seasmith in the 44th Season of Wizardry<br>
