nd just prior. I had to enlist the help of a rogue and shaman to cast sow on him as rogues cant sneak thru water without sow or they'll drown.<br>
<br>
As a sidenote, plan A: bringing along a group of 35-40s does not work (someone dies and it takes half the night to save them). Plan B: Wiz IVU does not work (it is 40+ MOB drop only). So plan C: high level help is the only real effective method. Otherwise, Plan D: Kamikaze death is your only option.<br>
<br>
But hay, I got the +10 INT and thats what counts!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umagiw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magiw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/02 12:04:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower Guk Strategies</span><hr size=1> I found that a 10 dose IVU potion was more than enough to get me to the Hand room solo and if you go for the rod when people are camping room, you don't have to worry about invising yourself to swim up to the rod. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umontigo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Montigo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/02 1:14:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower Guk Strategies</span><hr size=1> I'm lvl 47 now would I be able to just walk in a snag it with no aggro?.<br>
